────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Interpretation
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * Transformer and LNN baselines overfit to training distribution but generalise
   poorly (~45% token / ~2% sequence on held-out). MT-LNN's inductive biases
   (13 protofilaments, GTP renewal, RMC coupling, MAPGate) give it a large
   generalisation gap at matched parameter count.
 * Only MT-LNN responds to anesthesia. The hooks attach exclusively to MT-DL
   and the GlobalCoherenceLayer -- both absent in the baselines -- so the
   Phi_hat delta for Transformer / LNN is exactly 0.
 * Anesthesia thus acts as an architectural fingerprint: it can distinguish
   MT-LNN from architecturally-similar models at inference time.

